HEADWORD: Pneumaticity
<hw>Pneu`ma*tic"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The state of being pneumatic, or of having a cavity or cavities
filled with air; <as>as, the <ex>pneumaticity</ex> of the bones of
birds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pneumatics</ent>⟦br⟧
